body: "## Charter\nLiving log of Architecture Decision Records. Each ADR is a Decision item under this epic capturing context, the decision, consequences, and evidence for an architectural choice. The log includes both proposed ADRs (open) and accepted historical records (closed).\n\n## Conventions\n- ADR titles: \"ADR: <date or topic> — <decision>\".\n- Open ADRs are proposals under active review; they may be edited before acceptance.\n- Closing an ADR means the decision text is accepted as architecture context, not that every implementation child has shipped. Implementation remains tracked by the linked epics/features/tasks.\n- Accepted/closed ADRs are historical records: do not rewrite their decision text retroactively; append comments or create a superseding ADR instead.\n- Current open children: pm-96wm (2026-06-07 deep-audit ADR remediation verification), pm-pbyu (noun-verb CLI grammar), and pm-muhw (SDK public API layering).\n\n## Update 2026-07-05\nTwo new proposed ADRs added to the log: pm-pbyu (noun-verb CLI grammar + alias-preserving deprecation policy, for epic pm-n7rr) and pm-muhw (SDK is the public programmatic API; CLI/MCP become presentation layers as primitives are promoted, for epic pm-usfg). Open = proposed; close = accepted."
